bug.short_desc: usability: blivet-gui greyed items in adding partition dialog
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1269192 Screenshot
Description of problem: When adding a new partition(or btrfs volume etc.) many of the labels are greyed out but not disabled. This is highly confusing as greyed labels usually mark fields that are unusable/not supported etc.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): Fedora 26 alpha
How reproducible: always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Run installation and visit blivet-gui. 2. Choose "+" on free space 3.
Actual results: Some labels are greyed out despite not being disabled.
Expected results: All labels for active/available fields are in normal "black" styled text.
